WHO   — Ben Selleck — the lot at stake
WHAT  — The home on the line: the decent man whose lot — and family livelihood — the whole hustle is meant to rescue.
WHERE — GDS · The Goods (2009)  Framework inputs: The Goods: Live Hard, Sell Hard (2009, dir. Neal Brennan, Gary Sanchez/Paramount Vantage); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the parable needs real stakes — a family business that the cynical sale might actually save.
HOW   — By gambling his struggling lot on a crew of mercenary closers as a last resort.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  Forty years I built this lot. I hired the sharks because the alternative was losing all of it. Save it. Please.

